"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/90962","Cabinet Office","false","2014-09-11","<p>The Cabinet Office Efficiency and Reform Group was formed in June 2010 to drive reforms that improve public services, deliver savings and reduce wasteful expenditure.</p><p>On 10 June my Right Honourable Friend the Chancellor and I announced savings through efficiency and reform of central government of £14.3bn for 2013-2014 against a 2009/10 baseline. These savings are both recurring and non-recurring items and include £5.4bn from procurement and commercial savings, £3.3bn in project savings and £4.7bn from workforce reform and pensions savings.</p><p> </p>","Horsham","Mr Francis Maude",,"2014-09-11T14:26:27.730594Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/90962/answer","Biography information for Lord Maude of Horsham","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/90962/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/90962/answer",,,,,"53","Cabinet Office","Cabinet Office","2014-09-08","Government Departments: Cost Effectiveness","1","House of Commons","To ask the Minister for the Cabinet Office, what recent steps he has taken to reduce waste across Government.","false","Biography information for Justin Tomlinson","North Swindon","Justin Tomlinson","208558"
