"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/90994","Department for Education","false","2014-09-11","<p>Free school projects are not approved to open in any specific year. The ‘planned opening date’ may change during pre-opening, sometimes at the request of proposers. These changes are part of the normal process of setting up new schools.</p><p>10 free schools that planned to open in September 2014 were deferred before 1 March 2014:</p><ol><li>Burlington Danes Primary Academy</li><li>City Gateway Hackney</li><li>City Gateway Newham</li><li>NAS Church Lawton School</li><li>NAS Vanguard School</li><li>The Bridge Integrated Learning Space</li><li>The Kingston Academy</li><li>The University of Birmingham School and Sixth Form</li><li>Walthamstow Primary Academy</li><li>West Reading Education Network (WREN) Secondary School</li></ol><p>14 free schools that planned to open in September 2014 were deferred after 1 March 2014:</p><ol><li>ARK Byron Primary Academy</li><li>ARK North Enfield Academy</li><li>ARK Pioneer Academy</li><li>Falcons Primary School</li><li>Gateway Academy</li><li>Gladstone School</li><li>Harperbury Free School</li><li>Harris Primary Academy Beckenham</li><li>Khalsa Engineering Academy</li><li>Milton Keynes Free School</li><li>Oasis Academy Romford</li><li>Pentland Special School</li><li>The Legatum Academy</li><li>Turing House School</li></ol>","Crewe and Nantwich","Mr Edward Timpson",,"2014-09-11T16:05:22.646304Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/90994/answer","Biography information for Edward Timpson","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/90994/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/90994/answer",,,,,"60","Education","Education","2014-09-08","Free Schools","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Education, which Free Schools that had planned to open in September 2014 have had their opening delayed (a) since they were pre-approved and (b) since 1 March 2014.","false","Biography information for Mr Jim Cunningham","Coventry South","Mr Jim Cunningham","208475"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/90995","Department for Education","false","2014-09-11","<p>The following table provides the information available for the percentage of teachers in publicly funded schools in England who do not hold a degree and the percentage of teachers for whom qualifications data was provided.</p><p> </p><table><tbody><tr><td> </td><td><p>Percentage recorded with no degree level qualification</p></td><td><p>Percentage for whom qualification information was provided</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2013</p></td><td><p><em>3.3%</em></p></td><td><p><em>94.0%</em></p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2012</p></td><td><p><em>3.9%</em></p></td><td><p><em>93.7%</em></p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2011</p></td><td><p><em>5.1%</em></p></td><td><p><em>91.2%</em></p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2010</p></td><td><p><em>5.7%</em></p></td><td><p><em>90.1%</em></p></td></tr></tbody></table><p> </p><p>Source: School Workforce Census</p><p> </p>","Yeovil","Mr David Laws",,"2014-09-11T11:40:39.2152675Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/90995/answer","Biography information for Mr David Laws","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/90995/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/90995/answer",,,,,"60","Education","Education","2014-09-08","Teachers: Qualifications","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Education, how may teachers in state-funded schools did not hold a degree in (a) 2010, (b) 2011, (c) 2012 and (d) 2013.","false","Biography information for Mr Jim Cunningham","Coventry South","Mr Jim Cunningham","208477"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/90996","Department for Education","false","2014-09-11","<p> </p><p>All schools are required, by law, to have a behaviour policy with measures to address all forms of bullying, including homophobic bullying. We trust schools and teachers to decide what measures they should use to address homophobia based on their particular circumstances.</p><p>Schools are held to account by Ofsted for their effectiveness in managing pupil behaviour and safety, which includes homophobic bullying. Inspectors must consider pupils’ freedom from all forms of harassment, bullying and discrimination. As part of the inspection, schools are asked to make available evidence of records and analysis of bullying, in particular homophobic bullying.</p><p>We have issued advice to schools on preventing and tackling bullying in which we link to national organisations such as Stonewall, who can provide specialist advice to schools. This advice is available online at: <a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/publications/preventing-and-tackling-bullying" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/publications/preventing-and-tackling-bullying</a></p><p>In addition, we are working closely with the Government Equalities Office on a research project looking at effective ways of preventing and tackling homophobic, biphobic and transphobic bullying in schools. The results of the first phase of this work are expected to be published in autumn.</p><p>The Government has not set any national targets for tackling homophobia in schools as targets can lead to perverse incentives with schools doing the minimum required to fulfil the target rather than tackling the issue.</p>","Bognor Regis and Littlehampton","Mr Nick Gibb",,"2014-09-11T15:12:54.3181907Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/90996/answer","Biography information for Nick Gibb","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/90996/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/90996/answer",,,,,"60","Education","Education","2014-09-08","Schools: Homophobia","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Education, what targets the Government has set for tackling homophobia in schools; and what steps have been taken to achieve those targets in the last 12 months.","false","Biography information for Gloria De Piero","Ashfield","Gloria De Piero","208535"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/90997","Department for Education","false","2014-09-11","<p>The Government has made good progress in increasing the proportion of 16-year-olds who are participating in education and training (which includes those combining employment with training). The latest figures,<a title="" href="http://3dcpri-papp09/new_parliamentaryquestion/208596-%20Stephen%20Timms/Draft/208596%20pq%20team%20qa%2010.9.14%20final.docx#_ftn1" target="_blank">[1]</a> published on 25 June 2014, show that 93.8% of 16-year-olds were participating in education or work-based learning at the end of 2013, which is the highest figure since consistent records began in 1994. This represents an increase of 2.8 percentage points on the previous year, the largest increase observed over this period.</p><p>The Government will continue to encourage further improvements in participation and plans to spend £7.2 billion in 2014-15 to fund an education and training place for every 16- and 17-year-old who wants one. However, there will always be a small proportion of young people who are not in education, employment and training (NEET) due to personal circumstances such as illness.</p><p><a title="" href="http://3dcpri-papp09/new_parliamentaryquestion/208596-%20Stephen%20Timms/Draft/208596%20pq%20team%20qa%2010.9.14%20final.docx#_ftnref1" target="_blank">[1]</a> Participation in education, training and employment, age 16 to 18 statistical first release <a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/statistics/participation-in-education-training-and-employment-age-16-to-18" target="_blank">www.gov.uk/government/statistics/participation-in-education-training-and-employment-age-16-to-18</a></p>","Grantham and Stamford","Nick Boles",,"2014-09-11T16:45:30.4048783Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/90997/answer","Biography information for Nick Boles","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/90997/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/90997/answer",,,,,"60","Education","Education","2014-09-08","Employment: Young People","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Education, when she expects her Department to meet its target of all 16 year olds being in employment, education or training.","false","Biography information for Stephen Timms","East Ham","Stephen Timms","208596"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/90998","Department for Education","false","2014-09-11","<p>We intend to publish the final allocation of initial teacher training (ITT) places for the 2014/15 academic year as management information in the coming weeks. Data on the initial allocation of places is published online at:</p><p><a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/publications/initial-teacher-training-allocations-for-academic-year-2014-to-2015" target="_blank">www.gov.uk/government/publications/initial-teacher-training-allocations-for-academic-year-2014-to-2015</a>.</p><p> </p>","Yeovil","Mr David Laws",,"2014-09-11T11:41:33.7497628Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/90998/answer","Biography information for Mr David Laws","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/90998/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/90998/answer",,,,,"60","Education","Education","2014-09-08","Teachers: Training","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Education, when the National College of Teaching and Learning will publish the final initial teacher training allocations for 2014-15.","false","Biography information for Tristram Hunt","Stoke-on-Trent Central","Tristram Hunt","208627"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/90999","Department for Education","false","2014-09-11","<p>The table attached shows the total number of trainee teachers in each region from 2010/11 to 2013/14.</p><p>This is taken from the initial teacher training (ITT) census, which is taken on the second Wednesday of October each academic year. Further information is published online at:</p><p><a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/statistics/initial-teacher-training-trainee-number-census-2013-to-2014" target="_blank">www.gov.uk/government/statistics/initial-teacher-training-trainee-number-census-2013-to-2014</a>.</p><p> </p>","Yeovil","Mr David Laws",,"2014-09-11T11:39:19.1207078Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/90999/answer","Biography information for Mr David Laws","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/90999/answer","208628. Trainee Teachers by Region PQ team Final Part 2 11.9.14.docx","208628. Trainee Teachers by Region PQ team Final Part 2 11.9.14.docx","Trainee Teachers by Region from 2010/11 to 2013/14","Trainee Teachers by Region from 2010/11 to 2013/14","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/90999/answer",,,,,"60","Education","Education","2014-09-08","Teachers: Training","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Education, what the final number of trainee teachers recruited in each region was in (a) 2010-11, (b) 2011-12, (c) 2012-13 and (d) 2013-14.","false","Biography information for Tristram Hunt","Stoke-on-Trent Central","Tristram Hunt","208628"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/91000","Department for Education","false","2014-09-11","<p>The requested information on the number of trainee teachers required in each region is not available.</p><p>Information on the number of initial teacher training (ITT) allocations and places requested for the 2014/15 academic year grouped by region is available in the “Initial teacher training allocations for academic year 2014 to 2015” publication (summary by region tab). This is published online at: <a href="http://www.gov.uk/government/uploads/system/uploads/attachment_data/file/300720/itt_allocations_management_information_21_nov_2013.xlsx" target="_blank">www.gov.uk/government/uploads/system/uploads/attachment_data/file/300720/itt_allocations_management_information_21_nov_2013.xlsx</a>.</p><p> </p>","Yeovil","Mr David Laws",,"2014-09-11T11:42:37.6309748Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/91000/answer","Biography information for Mr David Laws","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/91000/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/91000/answer",,,,,"60","Education","Education","2014-09-08","Teachers: Training","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Education, what estimate her Department has made of the number of trainee teachers required in each region in (a) 2010-11, (b) 2011-12, (c) 2012-13, (d) 2013-14 and (e) 2014-15.","false","Biography information for Tristram Hunt","Stoke-on-Trent Central","Tristram Hunt","208630"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/91001","Department for Education","false","2014-09-11","<p> </p><p>The ICT Mark was launched by the National Association of Advisers for Computers in Education (Naace) in 2007 and was accredited by Becta until 2011. Following the closure of Becta in 2011, Naace took full responsibility for awarding the ICT Mark independently of government, and the Department for Education ceased to have any involvement. According to Naace, 379 schools in the United Kingdom received the award in 2013.</p><p> </p>","Bognor Regis and Littlehampton","Mr Nick Gibb",,"2014-09-11T15:01:07.1806379Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/91001/answer","Biography information for Nick Gibb","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/91001/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/91001/answer",,,,,"60","Education","Education","2014-09-08","Schools: ICT","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Education, what the significance is of the award of an ICT Mark to a school; and how many schools received such an award in 2013.","false","Biography information for Mr Gregory Campbell","East Londonderry","Mr Gregory Campbell","208621"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/91002","Department for Education","false","2014-09-11","<p>There is no requirement for a particular number of trainee teachers to be recruited to School Direct places. We aim to recruit in line with the number of trainees needed across all routes, as estimated by our Teacher Supply Model.</p><p> </p><p>The Teacher Supply Model figures for the academic year 2014/15 have been published as part of management information about initial teacher training (ITT) allocations. This is published online at:</p><p><a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/publications/initial-teacher-training-allocations-for-academic-year-2014-to-2015" target="_blank">www.gov.uk/government/publications/initial-teacher-training-allocations-for-academic-year-2014-to-2015</a>.</p><p> </p>","Yeovil","Mr David Laws",,"2014-09-11T11:43:52.9872253Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/91002/answer","Biography information for Mr David Laws","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/91002/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/91002/answer",,,,,"60","Education","Education","2014-09-08","Teachers: Training","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Education, what estimate her Department has made of the number of trainee teachers required through the School Direct programme in 2014-15.","false","Biography information for Tristram Hunt","Stoke-on-Trent Central","Tristram Hunt","208629"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/91003","Department for Energy and Climate Change","false","2014-09-12","<p>The Green Deal Home Improvement Fund (GDHIF) is applied for by householders on a non means tested basis across England and Wales.</p><p>Currently the department has not published any geographic breakdowns on GDHIF, as these would form part of the more detailed quarterly series of statistics (<a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/collections/green-deal-and-energy-company-obligation-eco-statistics#quarterly-statistics" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/collections/green-deal-and-energy-company-obligation-eco-statistics#quarterly-statistics</a>).</p><p> </p>","Hastings and Rye","Amber Rudd",,"2014-09-12T13:07:49.1565297Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/91003/answer","Biography information for Amber Rudd","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/91003/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/91003/answer","Hastings and Rye","Amber Rudd","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/91003/answer/previousversion/19595","Biography information for Amber Rudd","63","Energy and Climate Change","Energy and Climate Change","2014-09-08","Green Deal Scheme","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Energy and Climate Change, what estimate he has made of the proportion of Green Deal Home Improvement funding that has been allocated to deprived areas.","false","Biography information for Graham P Jones","Hyndburn","Graham Jones","208505"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/91004","Department for Energy and Climate Change","false","2014-09-12","<p>I have had no such discussions.</p><p> </p>","West Suffolk","Matthew Hancock",,"2014-09-12T11:36:50.9998744Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/91004/answer","Biography information for Matt Hancock","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/91004/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/91004/answer",,,,,"63","Energy and Climate Change","Energy and Climate Change","2014-09-08","Offshore Industry","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Energy and Climate Change, what discussions he has had with (a) the Health and Safety Executive, (b) offshore trade unions and (c) Oil and Gas UK on accommodation standards for offshore oil and gas workers on installations in the North Sea.","false","Biography information for Alex Cunningham","Stockton North","Alex Cunningham","208466"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/91005","Department for Energy and Climate Change","false","2014-09-12","<p>Centrica has stated that they expect the average bill of British Gas customers to be £90 lower in 2014 compared to 2013 in their 2014 H1 Interim Results (available at this link.) <a href="http://www.centrica.com/files/results/interim14/2014_interim_results.pdf" target="_blank">http://www.centrica.com/files/results/interim14/2014_interim_results.pdf </a></p><p> </p>","West Suffolk","Matthew Hancock",,"2014-09-12T11:34:30.2992353Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/91005/answer","Biography information for Matt Hancock","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/91005/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/91005/answer","West Suffolk","Matthew Hancock","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/91005/answer/previousversion/19592","Biography information for Matt Hancock","63","Energy and Climate Change","Energy and Climate Change","2014-09-08","Energy: Prices","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Energy and Climate Change, pursuant to the statement by the Minister of State at his Department on 2 September 2014 in the Second Delegated Legislation Committee, that in winter 2013-14 average bills being paid by British Gas customers were £90 lower, what the evidential basis was for that statement.","false","Biography information for Julie Elliott","Sunderland Central","Julie Elliott","208471"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/91006","Department for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","false","2014-10-13","<p>Lord de Mauley discussed the ban on the import of mangoes from India with Commissioner Borg in the margins of the Environment Council on 22 June. On 24 and 25 June, the Defra Deputy Director for Plant Health and Chief Plant Health Officer discussed the issue with senior Commission officials.</p><p> </p><p> </p>","North Cornwall","Dan Rogerson",,"2014-10-13T15:38:00.207036Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/91006/answer","Biography information for Dan Rogerson","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/91006/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/91006/answer",,,,,"13","Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","2014-09-08","Mangoes: India","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs, what recent discussions her Department has had with EU institutions on the ban on the import of mangoes from India.","false","Biography information for Jonathan Ashworth","Leicester South","Jonathan Ashworth","208521"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/91007","Department for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","false","2014-10-13","<p>Since the ban was introduced, Defra officials and Lord de Mauley have had several discussions with UK trade representatives about the implications of the ban. The most recent meeting was on 22 July, when Lord de Mauley met with representatives of the National Asian Business Association, the Fresh Produce Consortium and other trade representatives together with the Indian High Commission. This focused on the importance of India demonstrating improvements in its phytosanitary export system to the European Union’s Food and Veterinary Office audit in September and what assistance could be provided to the Indian authorities.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p>The need for direct assistance to UK businesses has not been raised. However, the UK Government is making efforts to facilitate the resumption of trading in this highly valued product. For example, an Inspector from our Food and Environment Research Agency went to Mumbai to deliver a three day training event between 19 and 21 August. The training was aimed at exporters and government inspectors and was attended by nearly 200 delegates.</p><p> </p>","North Cornwall","Dan Rogerson",,"2014-10-13T15:36:53.385032Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/91007/answer","Biography information for Dan Rogerson","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/91007/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/91007/answer",,,,,"13","Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","2014-09-08","Mangoes: India","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs, what recent steps her Department has taken to help UK businesses adversely affected by the ban on the import of mangoes from India.","false","Biography information for Jonathan Ashworth","Leicester South","Jonathan Ashworth","208522"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/91008","Department for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","false","2014-10-13","<p>The lifting of the ban on the import of mangoes from India is a decision for the EU’s Standing Committee for Plant Health. This will be considered once India has demonstrated that it can meet European Union (EU) import requirements which are designed to prevent the introduction of plant pests. The EU’s Food and Veterinary Office was due to carry out a further audit of India’s phytosanitary export system between 2 and 12 September. The results of this audit will be published later in the year and the Standing Committee will then consider whether it is appropriate to lift the ban.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p>To help the Indian authorities ensure that future exports consistently comply with the EU’s requirements, Defra’s Food and Environment Research Agency delivered training to exporters and government inspectors in Mumbai in August.</p><p> </p>","North Cornwall","Dan Rogerson",,"2014-10-13T15:40:05.2611771Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/91008/answer","Biography information for Dan Rogerson","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/91008/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/91008/answer",,,,,"13","Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","2014-09-08","Mangoes: India","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs, what recent steps her Department has taken to reverse the EU ban on import of mangoes from India.","false","Biography information for Jonathan Ashworth","Leicester South","Jonathan Ashworth","208523"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/91009","Department for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","false","2014-09-11","<p> </p><p>The Independent Expert Panel concluded that they were confident that controlled shooting can be carried out safely, even in the context of protester activity. As with the first year of the culls, Best Practice Guidance for the controlled shooting of badgers is in place and compliance with this will be monitored by Natural England.</p><p> </p>","Camborne and Redruth","George Eustice",,"2014-09-11T10:47:48.857518Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/91009/answer","Biography information for George Eustice","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/91009/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/91009/answer",,,,,"13","Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","2014-09-08","Bovine Tuberculosis","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs, what recent assessment she has made of the effect of changes to safety requirements for the 2014 badger cull on the safety of that cull.","false","Biography information for Chris Williamson","Derby North","Chris Williamson","208550"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/91010","Department for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","false","2014-09-12","<p> </p><p>The cost of waste disposal should be borne by the operator of a waste management site, including clearance after a waste fire. The Environment Agency has various powers under the Environmental Permitting (England and Wales) Regulations 2010. It may serve notice on an operator who is in contravention of an environmental permit to take steps to remedy the situation, including the removal of waste. Where the Environment Agency considers that there is a risk of serious pollution from a regulated facility, it may take steps to remove the risk and charge back the costs to the operator.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p>Fire and Rescue Authorities have a statutory duty under section 7 of the Fire and Rescue Services Act 2004 to extinguish fires and to protect life and property in their areas. The Government has no plans to amend the legislation to enable Fire and Rescue Authorities to charge for these functions.</p><p> </p>","North Cornwall","Dan Rogerson",,"2014-09-12T11:44:34.1097167Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/91010/answer","Biography information for Dan Rogerson","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/91010/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/91010/answer",,,,,"13","Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","2014-09-08","Waste Disposal: Fires","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs, if she will bring forward proposals to ensure that licence holders not local authorities pay costs arising from fires at waste disposal sites.","false","Biography information for Justin Tomlinson","North Swindon","Justin Tomlinson","208571"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/91011","Department for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","false","2014-09-11","<p><br> The draft Rural Economy Impacts paper was an internal document that is not analytically robust. It has not been published and we have no plans to do so. The full list of references on which it was based has been released under Environmental Information Regulations. Redactions were made to the draft paper based on exceptions under the Environmental Information Regulations; Ministers were not involved in this process.</p><p> </p>","North Cornwall","Dan Rogerson","208611 ; 208612 ; 208613","2014-09-11T16:58:23.3851663Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/91011/answer","Biography information for Dan Rogerson","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/91011/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/91011/answer",,,,,"13","Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","2014-09-08","Fracking","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs, if she will place in the Library an unredacted copy of the Rural Community Policy Unit report on Shale Gas Rural Economy Impacts, published in March 2014.","false","Biography information for Lord Mann","Bassetlaw","John Mann","208622"
