"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/90591","Department for Business, Innovation and Skills","false","2014-10-01","<p>I very much welcome this initiative in Leeds to promote local economic growth and local businesses. UKTI is supporting a session on the Export Network.</p>","Tunbridge Wells","Greg Clark",,"2014-10-01T12:32:31.4331769Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/90591/answer","Biography information for Greg Clark","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/90591/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/90591/answer",,,,,"26","Business, Innovation and Skills","Business, Innovation and Skills","2014-09-04","Business: Leeds","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Business, Innovation and Skills, what steps he is taking to support Leeds Business Week.","false","Biography information for Greg Mulholland","Leeds North West","Greg Mulholland","208150"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/90592","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","false","2014-09-11","<p>The Government of Saudi Arabia faces a number of security challenges, with concerns arising from the fractious regional situation and external sources, and so have a legitimate requirement for types of equipment in the performance of its sovereign defensive responsibilities.</p><p>The Government remains confident that the UK has a thorough and robust export control and licensing system, which distinguishes between exports for legitimate defence and security purposes and exports that breach the Criterion 2 threshold: a clear risk that they might be used for internal repression, violation of human rights or gender-based violence. These considerations are specifically identified in the Government’s Consolidated EU and National Arms Export Licensing Criteria, Criteria against which all applications for strategic export control licences for military goods, including arms and dual-use goods are assessed on a case-by-case basis.</p><p>The Government is satisfied that the currently extant licences for Saudi Arabia are compliant with the UK’s export licensing criteria.</p>","Bournemouth East","Mr Tobias Ellwood",,"2014-09-11T08:55:41.4528656Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/90592/answer","Biography information for Mr Tobias Ellwood","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/90592/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/90592/answer",,,,,"16","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","2014-09-04","Arms Trade: Saudi Arabia","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Foreign and Commonwealth Affairs, if he will bring forward proposals to make military exports to Saudi Arabia contingent on human rights reform in that country.","false","Biography information for Greg Mulholland","Leeds North West","Greg Mulholland","208151"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/90593","Department for Business, Innovation and Skills","false","2014-09-09","<p> </p><p>Data on construction output is published by the ONS, in their statistical bulletin ‘Output in the Construction Industry’. This includes information on construction output for the regions of England, plus Scotland and Wales. No data for individual cities is published. This information has not been adjusted for inflation.</p><p> </p><table><tbody><tr><td> </td><td> </td><td> </td><td> </td><td> </td><td> </td></tr><tr><td colspan="6"><p><strong>Value of Construction Output: current prices (£ million)</strong></p><p><strong> </strong></p></td></tr><tr><td> </td><td><p><strong> </strong></p><p><strong>2009</strong></p></td><td><p><strong>2010</strong></p></td><td><p><strong>2011</strong></p></td><td><p><strong>2012</strong></p></td><td><p><strong>2013</strong></p></td></tr><tr><td><p> </p><p>England</p></td><td><p>97,068</p></td><td><p>102,005</p></td><td><p>106,456</p></td><td><p>102,195</p></td><td><p>106,468</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>West Midlands</p></td><td><p>8,243</p></td><td><p>9,158</p></td><td><p>8,927</p></td><td><p>8,329</p></td><td><p>9,347</p></td></tr><tr><td><p><em> </em></p><p><em>Source: ONS</em></p></td><td> </td><td> </td><td> </td><td> </td><td> </td></tr><tr><td> </td><td> </td><td> </td><td> </td><td> </td><td> </td></tr></tbody></table><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p>","Grantham and Stamford","Nick Boles",,"2014-09-09T14:13:52.5464712Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/90593/answer","Biography information for Nick Boles","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/90593/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/90593/answer",,,,,"26","Business, Innovation and Skills","Business, Innovation and Skills","2014-09-04","Construction","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Business, Innovation and Skills, what assessment he has made of the level of construction output in (a) Coventry, (b) the West Midlands and (c) England in each of the last five years.","false","Biography information for Mr Bob Ainsworth","Coventry North East","Mr Bob Ainsworth","208173"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/90594","Cabinet Office","false","2014-09-11","<p>Charity regulation is a devolved matter in Scotland and Northern Ireland.</p><p>The annual accounts of charities in England and Wales are available on the Charity Commission’s website but the data requested on funding sources is not routinely held. Some charities may include information about the source of their donations in their accounts but they are not required to do so.</p><p>The Charity Commission is alert to the potential abuse of humanitarian aid efforts through facilitating travel for individuals for other purposes, particularly to conflict zones where terrorist groups are known to operate or exert control, including in Syria and Iraq.</p><p>There is a risk that charities working in certain areas, including those where so-called Islamic State militants operate, may be abused for non-charitable purposes. This is of serious concern to the Charity Commission. The Charity Commission has issued alerts to charities operating in these areas and advice to members of the public of how to give safely to ensure that their donations reach the intended charitable target. This information is available on the Charity Commission’s website.</p><p>Where there are concerns about suspected terrorist or extremist abuse connected to a charity the Charity Commission will support the Police in conducting criminal investigations.</p><p> </p>","Braintree","Mr Brooks Newmark","208329","2014-09-11T14:32:05.3369083Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/90594/answer","Biography information for Mr Brooks Newmark","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/90594/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/90594/answer",,,,,"53","Cabinet Office","Cabinet Office","2014-09-04","Charities","1","House of Commons","To ask the Minister for the Cabinet Office, what estimate he has made of the number of charities registered in the UK primarily or substantially funded from Middle Eastern sources; and if he will make a statement.","false","Biography information for Lady Hermon","North Down","Lady Hermon","208181"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/90595","Deputy Prime Minister","false","2014-09-11","<p>The Cabinet Office provides no such support.</p><p> </p>","East Surrey","Mr Sam Gyimah",,"2014-09-11T11:51:30.8455402Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/90595/answer","Biography information for Mr Sam Gyimah","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/90595/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/90595/answer",,,,,"58","Deputy Prime Minister","Deputy Prime Minister","2014-09-04","Electoral Register","1","House of Commons","To ask the Deputy Prime Minister, what support his Department gives to private citizens who take legal action against electoral registration officers who do not conduct door to door canvassing of those households that do not return electoral registration forms.","false","Biography information for Chris Ruane","Vale of Clwyd","Chris Ruane","208193"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/90596","Deputy Prime Minister","false","2014-09-11","<p>Every local authority in England and Wales has sent out a letter alerting electors to the changes in the electoral registration system, promoting and encouraging the uptake of online registration</p><p> </p>","East Surrey","Mr Sam Gyimah",,"2014-09-11T11:53:16.8644518Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/90596/answer","Biography information for Mr Sam Gyimah","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/90596/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/90596/answer",,,,,"58","Deputy Prime Minister","Deputy Prime Minister","2014-09-04","Electoral Register","1","House of Commons","To ask the Deputy Prime Minister, which local authorities have (a) promoted online registration and (b) not promoted online registration since its introduction.","false","Biography information for Chris Ruane","Vale of Clwyd","Chris Ruane","208194"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/90597","Deputy Prime Minister","false","2014-09-11","<p>The Cabinet Office has ongoing discussions with all local authorities about the capability of their IT systems to deal with electoral registration.</p><p> </p>","East Surrey","Mr Sam Gyimah","208200","2014-09-11T11:42:26.0730237Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/90597/answer","Biography information for Mr Sam Gyimah","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/90597/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/90597/answer",,,,,"58","Deputy Prime Minister","Deputy Prime Minister","2014-09-04","Electoral Register","1","House of Commons","To ask the Deputy Prime Minister, which local authorities have contacted his Department on the capability of their computer system to deal with electoral registration.","false","Biography information for Chris Ruane","Vale of Clwyd","Chris Ruane","208199"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/90598","Deputy Prime Minister","false","2014-09-11","<p>As an independent body established by Parliament, the Electoral Commission is overseen by the Speaker’s Committee.</p><p>The Electoral Commission’s corporate plan includes measures which relate to its effectiveness and to registration and it is the duty of the Speaker’s Committee to examine and approve its corporate plan.</p><p> </p>","East Surrey","Mr Sam Gyimah","208224","2014-09-11T11:49:52.9757477Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/90598/answer","Biography information for Mr Sam Gyimah","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/90598/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/90598/answer",,,,,"58","Deputy Prime Minister","Deputy Prime Minister","2014-09-04","Electoral Register","1","House of Commons","To ask the Deputy Prime Minister, if his Department will discuss with the Electoral Commission that body changing its target performance for completeness of the electoral register between 2014-15 and 2018-19 from completeness does not deteriorate to completeness is improved.","false","Biography information for Chris Ruane","Vale of Clwyd","Chris Ruane","208225"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/90599","Cabinet Office","false","2014-09-09","<p>The National Security Adviser is the Head of the National Security Secretariat within the Cabinet Office, which supports the National Security Council and the Prime Minister in the full range of national security issues across Government, including cyber security, and ensures that departmental work is effectively co-ordinated. The Office of Cyber Security and Information Assurance sits within the National Security Secretariat and has responsibility for coordinating work to achieve the aims of the UK Cyber Security Strategy and oversees the National Cyber Security Programme.</p><p> </p>","Horsham","Mr Francis Maude",,"2014-09-09T15:24:00.0425979Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/90599/answer","Biography information for Lord Maude of Horsham","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/90599/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/90599/answer",,,,,"53","Cabinet Office","Cabinet Office","2014-09-04","Cybercrime","1","House of Commons","To ask the Minister for the Cabinet Office, what role the National Security Adviser has in relation to cyber-security.","false","Biography information for Chi Onwurah","Newcastle upon Tyne Central","Chi Onwurah","208223"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/90600","Deputy Prime Minister","false","2014-09-11","<p>Data concerning the volumes of online and paper applications received are available on the following web page:</p><p> </p><p><a href="https://www.gov.uk/performance/register-to-vote" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/performance/register-to-vote</a></p>","East Surrey","Mr Sam Gyimah","208312","2014-09-11T15:28:17.457315Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/90600/answer","Biography information for Mr Sam Gyimah","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/90600/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/90600/answer",,,,,"58","Deputy Prime Minister","Deputy Prime Minister","2014-09-04","Electoral Register","1","House of Commons","To ask the Deputy Prime Minister, how many people have registered to vote online in each week since individual electoral registration was implemented.","false","Biography information for Chris Ruane","Vale of Clwyd","Chris Ruane","208230"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/90601","Deputy Prime Minister","false","2014-09-11","<p>The Cabinet Office has not taken any legal action against Electoral Registration Officers (EROs) who have failed to conduct door-to-door canvassing of households in response to the non-return of electoral registration forms.</p><p>Cabinet Office officials and the Electoral Commission closely monitor EROs to ensure they successfully implement their plans for the transition to Individual Electoral Registration, including door-to-door canvassing.</p><p> </p>","East Surrey","Mr Sam Gyimah",,"2014-09-11T11:39:04.3721409Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/90601/answer","Biography information for Mr Sam Gyimah","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/90601/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/90601/answer",,,,,"58","Deputy Prime Minister","Deputy Prime Minister","2014-09-04","Electoral Register","1","House of Commons","To ask the Deputy Prime Minister, what recent legal action his Department has taken against local authorities which have, on several occasions, not conducted door-to-door canvassing of households which do not return their electoral registration forms.","false","Biography information for Chris Ruane","Vale of Clwyd","Chris Ruane","208229"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/90602","Deputy Prime Minister","false","2014-09-11","<p>As an independent body established by Parliament, the Electoral Commission is overseen by the Speaker’s Committee.</p><p>The Electoral Commission’s corporate plan includes measures which relate to its effectiveness and to registration and it is the duty of the Speaker’s Committee to examine and approve its corporate plan.</p><p> </p>","East Surrey","Mr Sam Gyimah","208225","2014-09-11T11:49:52.9132072Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/90602/answer","Biography information for Mr Sam Gyimah","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/90602/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/90602/answer",,,,,"58","Deputy Prime Minister","Deputy Prime Minister","2014-09-04","Electoral Register","1","House of Commons","To ask the Deputy Prime Minister, if his Department will ensure the key indicators for the effectiveness of the Electoral Commission include the actual number and proportion of UK citizens who are registered to vote.","false","Biography information for Chris Ruane","Vale of Clwyd","Chris Ruane","208224"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/90603","Cabinet Office","false","2014-09-09","<p>The Deputy Prime Minister’s Office and the Prime Minister’s Office are integral parts of the Cabinet Office.</p><p>The tables below set out the highest and lowest full-time equivalent salaries paid by my Department and its public bodies, during the years specified:</p><table><tbody><tr><td><p> </p></td><td colspan="5"><p><strong>Cabinet Office</strong></p></td><td><p> </p></td></tr><tr><td><p> </p></td><td><p><strong>2009/10</strong></p></td><td><p><strong>2010/11</strong></p></td><td><p><strong>2011/12</strong></p></td><td><p><strong>2012/13</strong></p></td><td><p><strong>2013/14</strong></p></td><td><p><strong>2014/15</strong></p></td></tr><tr><td><p><strong>Min</strong></p></td><td><p>£15,938</p></td><td><p>£16,229</p></td><td><p>£16,229</p></td><td><p>£16,229</p></td><td><p>£16,807</p></td><td><p>£16,807</p></td></tr><tr><td><p><strong>Max</strong></p></td><td><p>£238,526</p></td><td><p>£238,526</p></td><td><p>£238,526</p></td><td><p>£190,000</p></td><td><p>£191,813</p></td><td><p>£193,923</p></td></tr><tr><td><p> </p></td><td><p> </p></td><td><p> </p></td><td><p> </p></td><td><p> </p></td><td><p> </p></td><td><p> </p></td></tr><tr><td><p> </p></td><td><p> </p></td><td><p> </p></td><td><p> </p></td><td><p> </p></td><td><p> </p></td><td><p> </p></td></tr><tr><td><p> </p></td><td colspan="5"><p><strong>Big Lottery Fund</strong></p></td><td><p> </p></td></tr><tr><td><p> </p></td><td><p><strong>2010/11</strong></p></td><td><p><strong>2011/12</strong></p></td><td><p><strong>2012/13</strong></p></td><td><p><strong>2013/14</strong></p></td><td><p><strong>2014/15</strong></p></td><td><p> </p></td></tr><tr><td><p><strong>Min</strong></p></td><td><p>£13,459</p></td><td><p>£12,632</p></td><td><p>£13,853</p></td><td><p>£13,853</p></td><td><p>£13,853</p></td><td><p> </p></td></tr><tr><td><p><strong>Max</strong></p></td><td><p>£140,000</p></td><td><p>£140,000</p></td><td><p>£141,400</p></td