es/90797/answer",,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2014-09-04","Pay","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, what the (a) highest and (b) lowest full-time equivalent salary paid by (i) his Department and (ii) its public bodies was in (A) 2010-11, (B) 2011-12, (C) 2012-13, (D) 2013-14 and (E) 2014-15; and if he will make a statement.","false","Biography information for Gareth Thomas","Harrow West","Mr Gareth Thomas","208295"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/90798","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2014-09-10","<p /> <p /> <p>DWP is engaged in numerous energy efficiency projects which can be split into two main types:-</p><p> </p><p>1) Site specific projects –Consumption information is analysed to identify buildings with high usage patterns, which have the scope to offer significant savings from implementing a range of projects such as lighting improvements.</p><p> </p><p>2) Technical projects – focusing on energy saving products across the estate such as installation of Passive Infrared (PIR) sensors onto hot water boilers, Thermostatic Radiator Valves (TRV), and installation of Automatic Meter Readers which provide accurate, real time energy consumption data facilitating targeted action on high consumption buildings.</p><p> </p><p>DWP’s network of volunteer “Environmental Champions” continue their essential role in encouraging colleagues to save energy, supported by an interactive e-learning package for all staff, providing guidance on how to reduce energy consumption.</p>","Thornbury and Yate","Steve Webb",,"2014-09-10T12:05:47.3993745Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/90798/answer","Biography information for Steve Webb","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/90798/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/90798/answer",,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2014-09-04","Energy","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, what steps he is taking to reduce energy costs in his Department; and if he will make a statement.","false","Biography information for Simon Kirby","Brighton, Kemptown","Simon Kirby","208351"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/90799","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2014-09-10","<p /> <p /> <p>Since 1998 the Department for Work and Pensions occupies the majority of its accommodation under a Private Finance Initiative (PFI) known as the PRIME Contract.</p><p> </p><p>Under the terms of this PFI, the Department leases back fully serviced accommodation from its private sector partner Telereal Trillium. We pay an all-inclusive unitary price, known as the Facility Price (FP), for all our furniture, fixtures, equipment and services provided, including televisions.</p><p> </p><p>There were however, televisions supplied to the Department which fell outside the scope of the contract price; the costs of which are detailed below:</p><p> </p><p>(a) 2013 - two televisions at a cost of £487;</p><p> </p><p>(b) 2014 to date - four televisions at cost of £1,076.</p>","Thornbury and Yate","Steve Webb",,"2014-09-10T12:10:45.799304Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/90799/answer","Biography information for Steve Webb","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/90799/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/90799/answer",,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2014-09-04","Television","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, how much his Department spent on the purchase of televisions in (a) 2013 and (b) 2014 to date.","false","Biography information for Mr Ben Bradshaw","Exeter","Mr Ben Bradshaw","208323"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/90800","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2014-09-09","<p /> <p /> <p>Ministers and officials continuously engage with a wide range of organisations to help shape and inform policies.</p><p>Checking whether any member of staff from across the Department for Work and Pensions has held any discussions with the Poverty Truth Commission would involve disproportionate cost.</p>","Forest of Dean","Mr Mark Harper",,"2014-09-09T11:15:16.4597849Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/90800/answer","Biography information for Mr Mark Harper","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/90800/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/90800/answer",,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2014-09-04","Poverty Truth Commission","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, what discussions his Department has had with the Poverty Truth Commission.","false","Biography information for Stephen Timms","East Ham","Stephen Timms","208356"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/90801","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2014-09-09","<p>The Department is fully committed to the development of its staff by investing in learning to create a highly skilled, motivated and flexible workforce. The Department fully supports the Civil Service Reform Plan commitment to provide at least five days a year investment in learning and development for all Civil Servants. Further learning activity has been generated by the DWP Annual Skills Review, the development of a departmental Capability Plan and an increased training requirement necessary to support the DWP Welfare Reform agenda.</p><p>The Departmental spend per head is shown below and has been calculated by dividing the total annual spend for DWP by the staff in post figure for the years in question.</p><p>a) 2010-11 £110.40</p><p>b) 2011-12 £ 85.27</p><p>c) 2012-13 £ 58.80</p><p>d) 2013-14 £ 91.32</p>","Thornbury and Yate","Steve Webb",,"2014-09-09T15:37:07.9789014Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/90801/answer","Biography information for Steve Webb","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/90801/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/90801/answer",,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2014-09-04","Training","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, how much was spent per head on training staff of his Department in (a) 2010-11, (b) 2011-12, (c) 2012-13 and (d) 2013-14.","false","Biography information for Stephen Timms","East Ham","Stephen Timms","208357"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/90802","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2014-09-10","<p /> <p>Holding reply issued on 9th September 2014.</p><p>The Minister for Employment discussed ending the Youth Contract Wage Incentive Scheme and identified opportunities to help the most disadvantaged young people with the Minister of State for Skills and Enterprise</p>","Thornbury and Yate","Steve Webb",,"2014-09-10T11:55:12.5575375Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/90802/answer","Biography information for Steve Webb","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/90802/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/90802/answer","Forest of Dean","Mr Mark Harper","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/90802/answer/previousversion/19211","Biography information for Mr Mark Harper","29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2014-09-04","Employment Schemes: Young People","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, what discussions he has had with the Secretary of State for Education about ending the Youth Contract Wage Incentive scheme.","false","Biography information for Stephen Timms","East Ham","Stephen Timms","208358"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/90803","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2014-09-09","<p /> <p>The Department keeps security arrangements under constant review, amending these in the light of prevailing circumstances, and taking account of advice from the relevant security authorities. Beyond this, for obvious reasons, it would not be appropriate to comment further.</p>","Thornbury and Yate","Steve Webb",,"2014-09-09T11:03:40.7520162Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/90803/answer","Biography information for Steve Webb","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/90803/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/90803/answer",,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2014-09-04","Jobcentres: Security","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, what recent assessment he has made of the security of staff at Jobcentre Plus offices.","false","Biography information for Stephen Timms","East Ham","Stephen Timms","208359"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/90804","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2014-09-09","<p /> <p /> <p>I refer the Hon. Member to the Written Answer given by the Minister for Employment which was provided to the Hon. Member for North West Leicestershire (Andrew Brigden) on 1 September 2014, Official Report, column 41W.</p>","Thornbury and Yate","Steve Webb",,"2014-09-09T14:38:34.8237589Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/90804/answer","Biography information for Steve Webb","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/90804/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/90804/answer",,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2014-09-04","Social Security Benefits","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, what assessment he has made of the effectiveness of the current level of the benefit cap; and if he will make a statement.","false","Biography information for Simon Kirby","Brighton, Kemptown","Simon Kirby","208147"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/90805","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2014-09-09","<p /> <p>The Secretary of State or his ministers have not had any specific discussions with Ministers in the Department for Business, Innovation and Skills solely about the proposed reform of apprenticeships. Neither are any of the department’s officials sitting on programme boards managing the reform.</p>","Forest of Dean","Mr Mark Harper",,"2014-09-09T14:17:03.9353456Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/90805/answer","Biography information for Mr Mark Harper","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/90805/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/90805/answer",,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2014-09-04","Apprentices","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, what discussions he and Ministers in his Department have had with Ministers in the Department for Business, Innovation and Skills on the proposed reform of apprenticeships; what effect those discussions will have on his Department's projects and the work of their supply chain; and whether officials in his Department sit on programme boards managing the reform.","false","Biography information for Alex Cunningham","Stockton North","Alex Cunningham","208214"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/90806","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2014-09-11","<p /> <p>The Secretary of State for Work and Pensions is unable to provide the requested information as the DS1500 is completed by various Health Care Professionals from across the UK and the Department is not required to capture this level of Management Information.</p>","Forest of Dean","Mr Mark Harper",,"2014-09-11T16:17:32.9743045Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/90806/answer","Biography information for Mr Mark Harper","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/90806/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/90806/answer",,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2014-09-04","Terminal Illnesses: Scotland","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, how many people in Scotland have had DWP form DS1500 signed by their doctor to confirm they are terminally ill in the latest period for which figures are available.","false","Biography information for Dame Anne Begg","Aberdeen South","Dame Anne Begg","208206"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/90807","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2014-09-09","<p /> <p>The Department cannot respond to the House of Commons with regards to a specific case. I will write to my hon. Friend.</p>","Forest of Dean","Mr Mark Harper",,"2014-09-09T16:47:58.1045735Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/90807/answer","Biography information for Mr Mark Harper","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/90807/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/90807/answer",,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2014-09-04","Personal Independence Payment","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, when a decision will be made on the application made in November 2013 by Mrs Staltmeier of Christchurch for a personal independence payment.","false","Biography information for Sir Christopher Chope","Christchurch","Mr Christopher Chope","208252"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/90872","Ministry of Justice","false","2014-09-10","<p>Government departments are currently in transition from the 30 year rule for transferring records to The National Archives to a 20 year rule, over a ten year period. The National Archives works closely with departments to help them meet their targets for transferring records through published statistics and capability assessments.</p><p> </p><p>In March 2014 the Prime Minister commissioned his independent adviser on ministerial standards, Sir Alex Allan, to establish the position across government on the annual release of papers and the ability and readiness of departments to meet the requirements of moving to the 20-year rule. The Government will consider Sir Alex’s recommendations in due course.</p><p> </p>","Bermondsey and Old Southwark","Simon Hughes",,"2014-09-10T10:13:42.3791684Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/90872/answer","Biography information for Simon Hughes","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/90872/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/90872/answer",,,,,"54","Justice","Justice","2014-09-04","Public Records","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Justice, what steps he is taking to ensure that departments meet targets for clearing public records for transfer to the National Archives.","false","Biography information for Lord Beith","Berwick-upon-Tweed","Sir Alan Beith","905297"
